chers, as well as being of interest to students, policymakers and stakeholders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEducation, BilingualzSouth America. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzSouth America. 0aLanguage policyzSouth America. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh  aEnglish language learners.  aEnglish language policies.  aEnglish language teaching.  aGlobalisation.  aGlobalization.  aMinority languages.  aPolicy.  aSouth America.  aclassroom-based research.  ateacher preparation.1 aAbrahams, Mary Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlmeida, Danielle Barbosa Lins de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanfi, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarbeito, M. Celina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrovetto, Claudia A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChacón, Carmen T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDíaz Maggioli, Gabriel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJorge, Míriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamhi-Stein, Lía D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamhi-Stein, Lía D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKuhlman, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaggioli, Gabriel Díaz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOliveira, Luciana C. de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlivero, M. Matilde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPozzi, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/